{
  "doc_id": "44848",
  "text": "In recent times, flavonoids have been investigated in the treatment of ischaemic stroke and in reducing chronic vascular disease (CVD) mortality [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Flavonoids are known to possess cardio-protective effects [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Several studies have demonstrated the effect of dietary flavonoids and polyphenols on human health and disease. In the cardiovascular system, flavonoids influence the endogenous regulation of cholesterol synthesis and are known to scavenge free radicals. They have also been discovered to promote endothelial-derived relaxation factor-induced relaxation in rabbit arteries in vitro [CITATION_6] .",
